Experiment 7: Menu Program (Cut, Copy, Paste, Delete, Select All, Unselect All)
Aim

To create a program that implements a menu-driven interface with editing options such as Cut, Copy, Paste, Delete, Select All, and Unselect All for handling text data.

Algorithm
1.Start the program
2.Initialize variables
    Declare a string variable to store the text.
    Declare another variable for clipboard (temporary storage).
    Use a flag or variable to track selection.
3.Display menu options
   Show the following choices:
      Cut
      Copy
      Paste
      Delete
      Select All
      Unselect All
      Exit
4.Accept user choice
5.Perform operation based on choice
  Cut
     If text is selected:
     Copy selected text to clipboard
     Remove selected text from main text
  Copy
     If text is selected:
     Copy selected text to clipboard
  Paste
     Insert clipboard content into the text
  Delete
     Remove selected text from main text
  Select All
     Mark entire text as selected
  Unselect All
     Remove selection
  Exit
     Terminate the program
6.Display updated text
7.Repeat steps 3–6 until user selects Exit
8.Stop the program
